<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 'collective redundancies' means dismissals effected by an employer for one or more reasons not related to the individual workers concerned where, according to the choice of the Member States, the number of redundancies is: </inglise>
<eesti> a) kollektiivsed koondamised - t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastamine &uuml;hel v&otilde;i mitmel p&otilde;hjusel, mis ei ole seotud asjaomaste &uuml;ksikt&ouml;&ouml;tajate isikuga ning mille puhul vastavalt liikmesriigi valikule koondatakse: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) either, over a period of 30 days: </inglise>
<eesti> i) 30 p&auml;eva jooksul kas: </eesti>
<inglise> - at least 10 in establishments normally employing more than 20 and less than 100 workers, </inglise>
<eesti> - v&auml;hemalt 10 t&ouml;&ouml;tajat ettev&otilde;ttes, kus on tavaliselt &uuml;le 20 ja alla 100 t&ouml;&ouml;taja, </eesti>
<inglise> - at least 10 % of the number of workers in establishments normally employing at least 100 but less than 300 workers, </inglise>
<eesti> - v&auml;hemalt 10% t&ouml;&ouml;tajatest ettev&otilde;ttes, kus on tavaliselt v&auml;hemalt 100, kuid alla 300 t&ouml;&ouml;taja, </eesti>
<inglise> - at least 30 in establishments normally employing 300 workers or more, </inglise>
<eesti> - v&auml;hemalt 30 t&ouml;&ouml;tajat ettev&otilde;ttes, kus on tavaliselt 300 ja rohkem t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) or, over a period of 90 days, at least 20, whatever the number of workers normally employed in the establishments in question; </inglise>
<eesti> <hi rend="sub"> i </hi> ii) v&otilde;i 90 p&auml;eva jooksul v&auml;hemalt 20 t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, s&otilde;ltumata sellest, milline on tavaliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tajate arv selles ettev&otilde;ttes; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 'workers' representatives' means the workers' representatives provided for by the laws or practices of the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> b) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajad - t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajad vastavalt liikmesriikide seadustele v&otilde;i tavale. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of calculating the number of redundancies provided for in the first subparagraph of point (a), terminations of an employment contract which occur on the employer's initiative for one or more reasons not related to the individual workers concerned shall be assimilated to redundancies, provided that there are at least five redundancies. </inglise>
<eesti> Punkti a esimeses alapunktis s&auml;testatud koondamiste arvu m&auml;&auml;ramisel arvatakse koondamiste hulka ka sellised t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel toimunud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamised, mille &uuml;ks p&otilde;hjus v&otilde;i mitu p&otilde;hjust ei ole seotud asjaomaste &uuml;ksikt&ouml;&ouml;tajatega, juhul kui koondamisi on v&auml;hemalt viis. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
